---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { t } from '../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="Terms of Use" locale={locale}>
  <main class="site-main">
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h1 class="section-title">Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="section-desc">Minimal, honest, and legally clear.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-text">
        <p>By using Parallaxin, you agree to the following terms. We keep this as simple as possible:</p>

        <h3>1. Content & Licensing</h3>
        <p>
          All documentation and research content on this site is licensed under 
          <strong>CC-BY 4.0</strong>. You are free to share and adapt the material for any purpose, 
          even commercially, provided you give appropriate credit to Parallaxin.
        </p>

        <h3>2. Code</h3>
        <p>
          The source code for the Parallaxin platform is licensed under the 
          <strong>MIT License</strong>. You are free to use, copy, modify, and distribute the software.
        </p>

        <h3>3. No Warranty</h3>
        <p>
          While we strive for absolute accuracy and evidence-based reporting, we provide this 
          information "as is" without any legal guarantee. Use of the information is at your own risk.
        </p>

        <h3>4. No Legal Advice</h3>
        <p>
          Parallaxin is a platform for documentation and analysis. Nothing on this site constitutes 
          legal counsel or professional advice.
        </p>

        <h3>5. Jurisdiction</h3>
        <p>
          This content is hosted on GitHub (US) and is subject to United States law.
        </p>

        <h3>6. DMCA & Takedowns</h3>
        <p>
          We respond to valid DMCA takedown requests. However, please note that journalistic 
          documentation of public statements and actions by powerful actors is generally 
          protected use.
        </p>

        <h3>7. Privacy & Data</h3>
        <p>
          Parallaxin is built for privacy. We do not track you, we do not use cookies, and we 
          collect no personal data. There is no user data to request because none is stored.
        </p>

        <h3>8. Editorial Governance</h3>
        <p>
          Editorial decisions are governed by the 
          <a href={base + 'constitution'}>Parallaxin Constitution</a>, 
          not these terms.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .section {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .content-text {
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
  .content-text h3 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .content-text p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .content-text a {
    color: var(--color-documented);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .content-text a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
